About Ashley — Heredia & Lennon Family Law 0 Skip to Content Home Philosophy Attorneys About Ashley About Samantha Services Testimonials Blog FAQs Contact Us Open Menu Close Menu Home Philosophy Attorneys About Ashley About Samantha Services Testimonials Blog FAQs Contact Us Open Menu Close Menu Home Philosophy Folder: Attorneys Back Current Page: About Ashley About Samantha Services Testimonials Blog FAQs Contact Us ASHLEY HEREDIA Ashley Heredia has practiced law for over thirteen Prior to practicing family law, Ashley worked as a judicial staff attorney for the Superior Court of Cobb Ashley has also worked for some of Atlanta s most prestigious family law firms during her career, and was Partner at Hedgepeth, Heredia & In , Ashley opened her first law practice, Sawyer Family Law, in Roswell, Ashley managed this successful practice until opening Heredia & Lennon Family Ashley is a tireless advocate for her You can count on Ashley to be thorough, hardworking, and dedicated to your Ashley is known for giving candid and honest advice, but also providing the compassion and support her clients Ashley understands the toll litigation can take on a family and does everything possible to keep the process as seamless and as In all of her cases, Ashley strives to maximize a client s outcome while minimizing their costs, both financial and Ashley’s dedication and hard work is routinely recognized by her clients in her client testimonials . Ashley is also trained as a Guardian ad Litem (GAL), where she represents the best interests of a child or children in a contested custody If Ashley has been appointed to serve as a GAL in your case, you can easily schedule appointments with her via Ashley’s GAL online calendar . Ashley was born and raised in Marietta, Georgia, and currently resides in Atlanta neighborhood, When not working, Ashley enjoys traveling, live music and spending time with her daughter and her husband, a fellow family law Ashley s Online Scheduler “Family Law is deeply personal and can often times be very difficult for Clients can count on me to practice law with empathy and respect, and with honesty at the There may be times during my representation when I have to tell a client something they don’t want to While I deliver this news with compassion and professionalism, I will alway s be I believe one of the best things I can do as your attorney is to give you my honest feedback at every turn to ensure your expectations are properly set and you are never blindsided during what is already a difficult ” ~Ashley Education CUMBERLAND SCHOOL OF LAW, SAMFORD UNIVERSITY Juris Doctor, UNIVERSITY OF GEORGIA , Honors and Awards “Legal Elite”, Georgia Trend Magazine, “Rising Star” in Family Law, Atlanta Magazine and , Top Family Lawyer Under , National Academy of Family Law Attorneys Best Attorney Under , American Institute of Family Law Attorneys Award of Achievement for Outstanding Service to the Profession, State Bar of Georgia Graduate of the Young Lawyers Leadership Academy, State Bar of Georgia Graduate of the Institute of Family Law Associates, American Academy of Matrimonial Lawyers, Chicago, Illinois Legal Activities & Affiliations - CSG FAQ | Answers to Sports Card Grading Questions | CSG Menu Sign In Join About About CSG CSG Help Center FAQs Card Grading Holder & Label Grading Scale CSG Guarantee Submit Cards We Grade How to Submit Services & Fees News CSG Help Center For answers to frequently asked questions about sports card grading, CSG services and more, scroll To contact CSG Customer Service, click here . What sports cards will CSG grade? CSG will grade virtually all licensed and original sports cards that have been cataloged from the to the CSG will initially grade cards (2.5” x ”) as well as cards sized up to large vintage Topps cards (2-5 8” x 4”). CSG is planning to add more holder sizes soon to accommodate even more card Learn more Will CSG grade cards? CSG will focus on grading sports Its affiliate, CGC Trading Cards, focuses on grading trading CGC Trading Cards currently grades Pokémon and Magic: The Gathering cards, but additional card types may be accepted in the For more information, visit What do the CSG grades mean? CSG uses a highly accurate grading scale, with grades ranging from Perfect (a card graded with four ) to 1 (Poor). To determine a card s grade, CSG graders consider factors such as centering, manufacturing and handling defects, how well the card has been preserved, scuffing, indentations, soiling, fading and Learn more Does CSG offer ? Yes, CSG offers for an additional $10 per The turnaround time for is tier +5 business What are ? are grades that provide further detail into a card s overall There are four : Centering, Corners, Edges and Learn more What types of technology does CSG incorporate into the grading process? CSG incorporates technology that assists the CSG graders in areas such as card measurement and the detection of alterations and For example, artificial intelligence (AI) helps to automate many of the aspects of grading, such as attributing a card and measuring its Meanwhile, forensic devices reveal alternations and hidden details using UV and infrared light, inspections and ink and paper Does CSG image cards that are submitted for grading? Yes, CSG images all graded cards after Soon, these images will be available to view on the CSG CSG also offers premium digital imaging as an service for This imaging service consists of accurate, images of the front and back of the card, shown encapsulated in its CSG The fee is $5 per Is grading by CSG guaranteed? Yes, sports cards are backed by the comprehensive CSG Guarantee of authenticity and grade, which provides collectors with greater security and The CSG Guarantee is the strongest of any sports card grading Learn more How long does CSG grading take? The length of time it takes to get sports cards certified depends on the grading tier you select when the cards are For example, the estimated turnaround time for WalkThrough submissions is 2 business days, while the estimated turnaround time for Economy submissions is business CSG is committed to providing the fastest turnaround times in the To see current turnaround times, visit the CSG Services & Fees page . Will CSG grade “thick” cards? At launch, CSG will not accept cards that are thicker than standard stock If you submit a thick card, it will not be encapsulated and will be returned with an “Ineligible Type” label and a refund of the grading fees Starting in April , CSG will accept cards that are up to mm These cards will be encapsulated in holders that will accommodate more thicknesses than any other sports card grading company’s As an added benefit, all of CSG’s holders will be Some examples of thick cards include, but are not limited to: Most game used memorabilia cards Panini Immaculate Panini National Treasures Panini Absolute Panini Prizm Panini Certified Topps Inception Topps Sterling UD SP Authentic Panini Origins Panini One Panini Select Panini Flawless Topps Triple Threads Upper Deck The Cup Topps Project Panini National Treasures Will the CSG holder protect my cards? The CSG holder will significantly improve the protection of your CSG has invested extensive time and resources to develop the hobby’s best holder for sports The result is a holder that provides superior optics showcase a card’s color and detail, the sturdy case resists impacts and ultrasonic welding safely holds the card in Does CSG grade altered cards? CSG will not assign a numeric grade to a card deemed altered however, a card deemed to be altered but authentic can be encapsulated as Authentic Does CSG grade “sheet cut” cards? No, CSG does not grade cards that are “sheet cut” or measure larger than the published catalog What is CSG CrossOver service? With CSG’s CrossOver service, a card in a PSA, Beckett or SGC holder is evaluated for CSG The card will be removed from its holder and encapsulated by CSG only if CSG believes that the card will receive a CSG grade that is the same or higher than the grade assigned by the other grading If CSG believes the card does not meet its standards for the grade, it will be returned in

Commission (“SEC”) has charged New York resident Mark Alan Lisser with fraud for operating at least two boiler rooms, on Long Island, New York, and in Boca Raton, The SEC’s complaint alleges that Lisser raised approximately $2.1 million from at least retail investors and misappropriated more than $900,000 of their Concurrently, the Attorney’s Office for the Eastern District of New York filed a criminal complaint in federal court charging Mark Lisser with wire fraud for lying to investors and potential investors to induce them to invest in “pre-IPO” shares of several The complaint further alleges that Lisser’s company, Knightsbridge Capital Partners, did not own enough shares to cover the sales that it made to Lisser was arrested this Iorio Altamirano LLP is investigating potential Massapequa, New York, and was one of three partners who operated Knightsbridge Private Partners According to FINRA, Lisser is not currently registered as a financial Previously, Lisser was affiliated with six firms, four of which were expelled from FINRA for the securities industry: Garden State Securities, from – Global Arena Capital Corp ( expelled ) from – Prestige Financial Center, ( expelled ) from – Westrock Advisors, ( expelled ) from – GunnAllen Financial, from – Harrison Securities, ( expelled ) from – Between October and January , Lisser was one of three partners in Knightsbridge Private Partners LLC, which operated a series of websites (specifically, “www.preipo.us,” “www.earlypreipo.com,” and ”preipopros.com.”) and used to solicit investments in purported shares of three Lisser, and salespeople that he directed in the boiler rooms, used sales tactics and solicited investors by misrepresenting that a fund purchased “pre-IPO” shares in three companies directly from employees of the However, at the time of the solicitations, Knightsbridge did not own any shares of these Subsequently, Knightsbridge purchased shares or interests in shares of the companies from third parties, not Knightsbridge never owned enough shares to cover the sales it had made to As a result of this fraud scheme, Lisser misappropriated more than $700,000 in investors’ Lisser used these Ungrowth hacks, 1 Reason to Stop Sending Automated Twitter DMs – Get Growth Skip to content Get Growth Stories on growth and startups Menu and widgets Search for: Recent Posts Helping Others, the Ultimate Growth Hack From 0 to $4M in Sales, Jesse Mecham and YNAB’s Story of Growth Ungrowth hacks, 1 Reason to Stop Sending Automated Twitter DMs 7 Tips to Gain More Twitter Followers A Manifesto on Growth for Startups Recent Comments How to Grow Your Business Faster on How to Grow Your Business Faster by Hiten Shah Microconf Hub - Notes and resources about the conference on How to Grow Your Business Faster by Hiten Shah Archives June May April Categories Growth Startups Stories of Growth Uncategorized Ungrowth Hacks Meta Log in Entries RSS Comments RSS Ungrowth hacks, 1 Reason to Stop Sending Automated Twitter DMs Are you ready? Here it is: they I could really wrap up this post right here and I’d be adding a lot of value to this beautiful Internet of But let me riff on this topic just a We are getting lots of new followers every day (Hey guys!) and we enjoy Twitter as a medium for sharing But a fair number of the people we follow have an automated process that sends us a DM or direct message like this: No offense to Carlos here, but we could not care less about No seriously, we REALLY don’t We are also not that interested in your FB page or some other manifestation of your You need to buy us dinner before you … Oh Not only do we not care, but it wastes our time to see And worse it is ruining Twitter’s direct message feature as yet another pipe to shove spam in our Canned direct messages for the Fail! Hey… wanna come over for dinner? Guess what we are having? Canned dark red kidney We’re not even using plates… everyone just gets a can and an Sounds delicious right? That is how these automated direct messages Luke Rated PG, as in pretty When someone follows you on Twitter it is very loose Here is what they are saying: I’m interested in hearing what you have to say on some level, but only when it is convenient for me (during those times you are perusing your Twitter feed). We are not instantly best friends or interested in some another way to follow We may want more at some point, but take it easy To connect on a deeper level you need to do real engagement (see #6 in 7 Tips to Gain More Twitter Followers ). You need to do some real cooking!! Not just handing me a can of beans and a can Bonus Section – How to turn off emails for Twitter Direct Messages What do you do when the TV is blaring and all you want is some peace and quiet? You turn it Unfortunately that is what it has come to with the emails we get from Twitter Time to turn off the If the spam you get from Twitter DMs has turned into a nuisance here is how to gently show it to the Go to Twitter Settings Screen by clicking the gear in upper right corner Click the Email Notifications tab on the left side of the screen Find the checkbox that says: “I’m sent a direct message” Uncheck (Click. Oh that felt good!) Now… make sure that you scroll to the bottom of the page and click “Save changes”. Ahhhhh now for some peace and quiet in my inbox (except for all those great emails about doing actual business and growth… keep those coming!!) Ungrowth Hacks I am sure there are some conversion from techniques like You may get a few more Facebook likes, or you may get an extra email subscriber or But what is the price in terms of being hostile to so many for such a small reward? This is why I am calling this an ungrowth It is something you do NOT want to do if you are looking for long term There are so many other ways you can add real value to new contacts that can lead to growth, you don’t need to resort to tactics like If you are doing this we still love you and want to find ways to connect and grow Unfortunately though if you try to connect via Twitter DMs at this point it will merely fall on deaf Your’s truly, Harris Reynolds, Specialist with The Ungrowth Police Posted on June 4, Author Harris Reynolds Categories Ungrowth Hacks Leave a Reply Cancel reply Your email address will not be Required fields are marked Comment Name Email Website Post navigation Previous Previous post: 7 Tips to Gain More Twitter Followers Next Next post: From 0 to $4M in Sales, Jesse Mecham and YNAB’s Story of Growth Proudly powered by WordPress   From 0 to $4M in Sales, Jesse Mecham and YNAB’s Story of Growth – Get Growth Skip to content Get Growth Stories on growth and startups Menu and widgets Search for: Recent Posts Helping Others, the Ultimate Growth Hack From 0 to $4M in Sales, Jesse Mecham and YNAB’s Story of Growth Ungrowth hacks, 1 Reason to Stop Sending Automated Twitter DMs 7 Tips to Gain More Twitter Followers A Manifesto on Growth for Startups Recent Comments How to Grow Your Business Faster on How to Grow Your Business Faster by Hiten Shah Microconf Hub - Notes and resources about the conference on How to Grow Your Business Faster by Hiten Shah Archives June May April Categorie

TAX BENEFITS - HARRIS ENERGY GROUP Skip to content HARRIS ENERGY GROUP Main Menu HOME ABOUT US OPERATIONS TAX BENEFITS NEWS FAQ OWNER LOGIN CONTACT INVESTMENTS Benefits of Oil and Gas Investing TAX ADVANTAGES When it comes to investments for investors, oil and gas investments produce significant tax benefits with the backing of the Domestic energy production offers a litany of tax benefits for investors who can offset “ordinary” or “passive” income Intangible Drilling Costs These costs include everything but the actual well Labor, chemicals, mud, grease and other miscellaneous items necessary for drilling are considered These expenses generally constitute % of the total cost of drilling a well and are % deductible in the year For example, if it costs $300,000 to drill a well, and if it was determined that % of that cost would be considered intangible, the investor would receive a current deduction of $225 Furthermore, it doesn’t matter whether the well actually produces or even strikes Tangible Drilling Costs Tangible costs pertain to the actual direct cost of the equipment installed in and around the well, and it would appear that under the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act, most types of these tangible equipment are % depreciable in the year placed in Active Passive Income The tax code specifies that a working interest in an oil and gas well is not considered to be a passive activity as long as you do not invest through an entity that limits your This means that net losses can be offset against other forms of income, such as wages, interest, capital gains, provided you have not limited your Small Producer Tax Exemptions This is perhaps the most enticing tax break for small producers and This incentive, which is commonly known as the “depletion allowance”, excludes from taxation % of all gross income from oil and gas wells, subject to the following The percentage depletion deduction is generally limited to the lesser of % of the taxable income before the depletion allowance (Code (d)(1)) or % of the taxable income from the property before the depletion This special advantage is limited solely to small companies and Any company that produces or refines more than ,000 barrels of oil per day is Entities that own more than 1,000 barrels of oil per day, or 6 million cubic feet of gas per day, are excluded as Lease Operating Costs These include lease operating costs, administrative, legal and accounting These expenses are % deductible in the year they are Alternative Minimum Tax All excess intangible drilling costs have been specifically exempted as a “preference item” for those classified as an independent producer on the alternative minimum tax (Generally defined as an individual or entity whose proportionate share is less than 1,000 barrels of oil per day and or six million cubic feet of gas per ) Their AMTI, however, may not be reduced by more than percent of the AMTI that would otherwise be determined if the taxpayer were subject to this intangible drilling cost preference and did not compute an alternative tax net operating loss Developing Energy Infrastructure This list of tax breaks effectively illustrates how serious the government is about developing the domestic energy Perhaps most telling is the fact that there are no income or net worth limitations of any kind for any of them other than what is listed above (i.e. the small producer ) Therefore, even the wealthiest investors could invest directly in oil and gas and receive all of the benefits listed above, as long as they limit their ownership to 1,000 barrels of oil per No other investment category in America can compete with the smorgasbord of tax breaks that are available to the oil and gas Investment Options There are several different avenues available for oil and gas These can be broken down into four major categories: mutual funds, partnerships, royalty interests and working Each has a different level of risk and separate rules for Mutual Funds While this method of investment contains the least amount of risk for the investor, it also does not provide any of the tax benefits listed Investors will pay tax on all dividends and capital gains, just as they would with other Partnerships There are several forms of partnerships that can be used for oil and gas Limited partnerships are the most common, as they limit the liability of the limited partner to the amount of the limited partner’s investment A limited partnership can be structured to provide partners the choice of whether to be a limited partner (subject to the passive loss rules) or a general partner wherein a partner could deduct losses against ordinary The aforementioned tax incentives are available on a The partner will receive a form each year detailing his or her share of the revenue and Royalties This is the compensation received by those who own the minerals where oil and gas wells are This income comes “off the top” of the gross revenue generated from the Mineral owners typically receive anywh

What is an accredited investor? An individual or an entity can generally qualify as an accredited investor if they meet at least one of the following criteria: – an individual with income exceeding $200,000 or joint income with his or her spouse of at least $300,000, in each of the last two years with the expectation to reasonably maintain the same level of income in the present year – an individual with a net worth exceeding $1 million, excluding the primary residence, either individually or jointly with his or her spouse – an entity that has assets exceeding $5 million that was not formed solely for the purpose of making the investment oran entity whose owners all satisfy 1, 2, or 3 The term accredited investor is subject to change as well as its criteria, please visit the SEC s website to learn more about who qualifies as an accredited Please visit the SEC s website to learn more about who qualifies as an accredited https: www.investor.gov introduction-investing general-resources news-alerts alerts-bulletins investor-bulletins updated-3 +1.201.786.6300 Main Street, Floor Hackensack, NJ Follow Veloce Capital Main
